%----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%	ABSTRACT
%----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begin{abstract}
\noindent This investigation aimed to determine the sensitivity of the proposed liquid argon time projection chamber (LArTPC) experiment, DUNE, to bound neutron - anti-neutron (\(\nnbar\)) oscillations: A rare baryon number violating process.\\
At this stage, an \(\nnbar\) selection algorithm has been constructed and performs with an efficiency of \(93.3\%\), a purity of \(86.4\%\) and eliminates \(80.4\%\) of atmospheric \(\nu\) background events.\\
The first constituent of the analysis was a \(\pi^0\) reconstruction algorithm which was successfully implemented with an efficiency of \(87.2\%\) and a purity \(91.0\%\). Primary particles were then grouped into candidate primary vertices and this was done correctly \(99.6\%\) of the time. The reconstructed \(\pi^0\)s were then added to these vertices before plotting their energy and particle composition distributions. The vertex distributions of simulated atmospheric background events were then compared with those of the \(\nnbar\) events to quantify the overall effectiveness of the algorithms.\\
\end{abstract}
\newpage
